      <tr><td>doc</td><td>The document being written</td></tr>
      <tr><td>oldDoc</td><td>The previous version &mdash; <code>null</code> for new documents</td></tr>
      <tr><td>user</td><td>The authenticated user (<code>UserContext</code>), or <code>null</code> for anonymous requests</td></tr>
      <tr><td>ctx</td><td>Server-provided helpers for checking materialized grant state</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p class="section-sub" style="margin-top:1rem;"><strong style="color:var(--fg)">UserContext:</strong></p>
  <div class="cmd cmd--ts">
    {<br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;userHandle: <span class="fn">string</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="c">// stable unique id &mdash; use for all auth checks</span><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;displayName?: <span class="fn">string</span> <span class="c">// display only &mdash; never use for identity checks</span><br/>&nbsp;&nbsp;isOwner: <span class="fn">boolean</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="c">// true when this user owns the vibe &mdash; use for management gates</span><br/>}
  </div>

  <p class="section-sub" style="margin-top:1rem;"><strong style="color:var(--fg)">Helpers (<code>ctx</code>):</strong> Opaque closures over materialized grant state. They throw or pass &mdash; you cannot enumerate channels, list members, or iterate grants.</p>
  <ul class="callout-list">
    <li><code>ctx.requireAccess(channelId)</code> &mdash; throws if user is not in the channel</li>
    <li><code>ctx.requireRole(roleName)</code> &mdash; throws if user does not have the role</li>
